-- Daimler Reduces Employee Regulations by Almost Half, FTD Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-02-06T21:31:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/daimler-reduces-employee-regulations-by-almost-half-ftd-reports.html
Daimler AG (DAI)  cut the number of
regulations to which employees must adhere to 1,000 from 1,800
to simplify its decision-making procedures and may cut them even
further, the Financial Times Deutschland  reported , citing
Christine Hohmann-Dennhardt, the board member with
responsibility for integration and rights.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at 
 cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 